						<summary>

						<p>On a golden palanquin.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1735, Śrīmukha, Kārttika śu 11, Bhṛiguvāra</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1813 A.D., November 4, Thursday</hi> (not Friday).</p>						

						<p>States that Tōḷikiniyāṉ (the palanquin), which was the offering of Vijayaraṅgachokkanāthanāyaka to the god Raṅganātha, having become dilapidated was repaired by Mr. George Francis Trevers, the collector. The weight of gold used is 39(3/4) seers and that of silver 70(1/2) seers. Published: <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XXIV, No. 641.</p>						

						</summary>
